From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] debug: bypass led_start() to test if LED init is the hang

WR_TRACE 2a_pre_led_start landed but 2b_post_led_start did not.
led_start() in led.c does:
    gpio_is_ready_dt + gpio_pin_configure_dt for led0/1/2
    LOG_INF("LEDs started")
None of those should block, so this is suspicious.

Replace `err = led_start()` with `err = 0` to bypass the call.
If main reaches WR_TRACE 3 / 4 / 5 / 6 with the bypass in place,
we know led_start is the culprit and can dig further.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/main.c
@@ -165,7 +165,8 @@ int main(void)
     LOG_PRINTK("\n");
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2a_pre_led_start\n");

-    err = led_start();
+    /* patch 0025: bypass led_start() to isolate hang */
+    err = 0;
     printk("WR_TRACE: 2b_post_led_start err=%d\n", err);
     if (err) {
         LOG_ERR("Failed to initialize LEDs (err %d)", err);
